                    <content-note style="NORMAL">Note: On 25 February 2022, in view of the Russian Federation’s military invasion of Ukraine, the Committee of Ministers suspended Russia’s rights of representation in both the Committee of Ministers and the Parliamentary Assembly. On 15 March Russia announced that it was to withdraw from the Council after the Parliamentary Assembly voted unanimously to reject its continued membership. On the following day the Committee of Ministers determined that Russia ceased to be a member of the Council, with immediate effect. Kosovo applied to join the Council on 12 May 2022. The Ministerial Committee voted in April 2023 to refer the application to the Parliamentary Assembly for consideration. In April 2024 the Assembly recommended that Kosovo should be invited to become a Council member; a final decision was to be taken by the Committee of Ministers.</content-note>
