     <int-org-section id="CE.IO.572" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
          <heading>Organization</heading>
          <heading-note>May 2024</heading-note>
          <int-org-section id="CE.IO.SUMMIT.1" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Summit Meeting</heading>
               <p>Heads of state or of government of member countries convened for the first time in October 1993, in Vienna, Austria. The Fourth Council of Europe Summit was held in May 2023, in Reykjavík, Iceland, on the theme `United around our values’.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="CE.IO.573" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Committee of Ministers</heading>
               <p>The Committee consists of the ministers responsible for foreign affairs of all member states (or their deputies). It decides all matters of internal organization, makes recommendations to governments and draws up conventions and agreements with binding effect; it also discusses matters of political concern, such as European co-operation and compliance with member states' commitments, in particular concerning the protection of human rights. The Committee meets weekly at deputy ministerial level (assisted by a Bureau of Ministers’ Deputies) and once a year (in May or November) at ministerial level. Six two-day meetings are convened each year to supervise the execution of judgments of the European Court of Human Rights. When deemed necessary the Committee of Ministers may authorize a high-level political conference of specialized ministers from member states, aimed at achieving the Council of Europe’s strategic objectives or responding to significant events relating to human rights, the rule of law or democracy. Chairmanship of the Committee of Ministers rotates on a six-monthly basis (17 May-13 November 2024: Lithuania; 13 November 2024-May 2025: Luxembourg).</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="CE.IO.579" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Secretariat</heading>
               <p>The secretariat incorporates the Secretariats and Registry of the institutions of the Council. There are Directorates of Political Affairs and External Relations; Legal Advice and Public International Law; Communications; Programme Co-ordination; Internal Oversight; and Programme and Budget. There are also the following Directorates-General: Human Rights and Rule of Law; Democracy and Human Dignity; and General Administration; and a Treaty Office.</p>
